tspan.tspan: Point at any card. Move it into the
DISCARD pile if it isn't there already.
Name a card from the DISCARD/
UNDRAWN piles. If that card is present,
add it to your hand.
"Yes, yes, yes! Can I tell you, this is the
greatest moment of my life? I promise,
promise that I won't set anything on fire.
You have my word on that! This is great!"
Blithering Fool
If your opponent plays an ability where
you end up LOSING any card *other*
than Old Coot, gain twice as many life
tokens as there are life tokens on this
card. Remove any life tokens presently on
this card after.
x1 - Organ Failure
Remove twice as many life tokens from
your opponent's pool as there are life
tokens on this card. Remove any life
tokens presently on this card after.
"Wait, what?"
Old Coot
Point at a card. That card
cannot be
USED or LOST
until the start of your
next turn.
x3 - Terrible Idea
Point at a card, and flip it over. You may
choose one ability from that card to play
for yourself.
You must also pay the
associated life token
cost with that card.
"This is just like the battle of... um. Hold
on, I'll get there in a second."
Overeager Tactician
Point at a card. Remove any number of
life tokens on that card, and place half of
those tokens (rounded down) on a card of
your choice.
Remove 2 life tokens from your
opponent's pool.
"I'm a better at swords than Benedict ever
was, you stupid jerks!"
Egomaniacal Fencer
Every time you swap cards with your
opponent, they take as much damage as
there are life tokens on the card you give
them. You also take as much damage as
there are life tokens on the card given to
you. Remove life tokens from both cards
after the swap.
x3 - Tax Evasion
Point at a card. SWAP that card with any
card in your hand.
"Everything is 100% legit, trust me."
Fraudulent Accountant
If your opponent plays an ability where
you end up LOSING this card, remove
twice as many life tokens from your
opponent's pool as there are life tokens on
this card.
x2 - Runcible Spoon
Name a card. If your opponent has that
card in your hand, they must show it to
you.
"I am a SORCERER of the weirding ways.
Best me if you... wait! Pick another card."
Muddled Magician
Point at 3 cards that are NOT in the
discard pile. Your opponent must pick
ONE to go into the discard pile.
Name a card. If your opponent has that
card, they must EITHER: DISCARD it,
pay 3
life tokens to keep it, or SWAP it for
this
card.
"I promise I can handle it, honest! Just...
don't trust me with anything important."
Rebellious Youth
At the end of your turn, gain as many life
points as you have horn duplicates. Horn
duplicates DO NOT count towards your
card total.
x2 - Honk
Remove ONE life token from your pool,
now representing a horn duplicate. If you
are forced to LOSE the horn duplicate,
discard it. If your opponent forces you to
SWAP the horn duplicate with any other
card, that card must remain where it is.
Horn duplicates remain in your hand if
this card is LOST.
"HONK!"
Horn Guy
Discard up to 3 cards from your hand.
You must skip your turn for as many
times as you discarded cards.
x2 - It's Nothing
Point at 2 cards and place them side by side
face-down. Do not shuffle them. Your
opponent must pick ONE to take. You
take the other.
"There's no problem with the castle walls!
I'm out there everyday and I see nothing."
Bumbling Patroller
If this card remains front-facing over by
the start of your turn, flip it back. Your
opponent loses as many life points as
cards they did NOT USE last turn.
Flip this card over.
"I'll deal with it later."
Useless Underminer
x3 - Disheartening Service
Point at up to 4 cards not in your hand,
and add them to your hand. For each card
you've drawn, gain 2 temporary life
tokens; they are removed after you have
played all your abilities, before you take
damage based on the number of cards in
your hand.
"And Josiah begat... someone."
Impious Pretender
If your opponent ever invokes a
REACTion, you may give them as many
cards as there are life tokens on this card
halved and rounded down.
x4 - Hangover
Name a card. If that card is NOT in the
discard, add it to your hand.
"This calls for a celebratory drink!"
Devious Drunkard
